                        </div> 
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p>As long as you recognise when a word is functioning as an adjective (i.e. that it is modifying a noun), and remember that
                    participles can function as adjectives, then you won't find them hard to deal with. 
                </p>
                <p>Finally, participles can function as nouns. For example, we might talk in modern English about 'the deceased' or 'the living'. 
                    In both cases, we are using a participle as a noun. Generally, if a participle is used as a noun, you will find it included as 
                    such in a dictionary. 
